04/05/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- EU envoy to Macedonia Erwan Fouere said on Wednesday (3 May) that the Union is prepared to play an active role in monitoring the 5 July parliamentary elections. The vote is seen as a crucial test of Macedonia's Euro-Atlantic integration bid. 
Also Wednesday, the State Election Commission adopted a code for domestic election monitors. It stipulates that observers must not display any party symbols, interfere in the election process, or influence election committees. (A1 TV, Telma TV - 03/05/06)
